<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p><em>Summary:</em>
When formatTimestamp() is given an integer representing a Unix timestamp, the resulting RFC 3339 date string is generated without a timezone offset relative to the system timezone. This can lead to confusion since Unix timezones are always with respect to UTC+0.</p>

<p>To avoid this, times generated from a Unix timestamp should always be generated using UTC and the timezone should be explicitly stated. Unit tests should be updated accordingly.</p>

<p><em>Regression:</em>
Introduced in r5036, affects 1.0.0 RC1 and 1.0.0 RC2.</p>

<p><em>Notes:</em>
Issue fixed and unit tests updated in my build. Patch sent to rboyd for review.</p>

